data.content:
Yes! MSTest v3+ supports **ValueTuples** with `DynamicData`, giving you compile-time type safety:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**Benefits:**
- Type mismatches caught at compile time (no runtime `InvalidCastException`)
- Named tuple elements serve as documentation
- No boxing of value types like `bool`

This requires **MSTest 3.4+** (`MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.Sdk`).
